# REST API Tests for STR Agentic Adventures Chat System
# Use the REST Client extension in VS Code to test these endpoints

### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000
@campaignId = test-campaign-123
@characterId = test-character-456

### Test 1: Verify backend is running
GET {{baseUrl}}/docs
Accept: text/html

###

### Test 2: Check API health
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/
Accept: application/json

###

### Test 3: List all campaigns
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/game/campaigns
Accept: application/json

###

### Test 4: Create a working character for testing
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/game/character
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Test Hero",
  "race": "Human",
  "character_class": "Wizard",
  "abilities": {
    "strength": 10,
    "dexterity": 12,
    "constitution": 14,
    "intelligence": 16,
    "wisdom": 13,
    "charisma": 11
  },
  "backstory": "A curious wizard eager to explore the world"
}

###

### Test 5: Create a test campaign
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/game/campaign
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Debug Campaign",
  "setting": "High Fantasy",
  "world_description": "A mystical realm perfect for testing chat functionality",
  "tone": "adventurous"
}

###

### Test 6: Test the main player input endpoint (this is what the frontend fallback uses)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/game/input
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "I cast a light spell to illuminate the dark corridor ahead",
  "character_id": "{{characterId}}",
  "campaign_id": "{{campaignId}}"
}

###

### Test 7: Test player input with simple message
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/game/input
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "Hello, what do I see around me?",
  "character_id": "{{characterId}}",
  "campaign_id": "{{campaignId}}"
}

###

### Test 8: Test player input with action
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/game/input
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "I want to search for hidden doors or secret passages in this room",
  "character_id": "{{characterId}}",
  "campaign_id": "{{campaignId}}"
}

###

### Test 9: Test with invalid character ID (should still work with fallback)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/game/input
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "Testing with invalid character ID",
  "character_id": "invalid-character-id",
  "campaign_id": "{{campaignId}}"
}

###

### Test 10: Test with missing required fields (should return 422)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/game/input
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "Missing character and campaign IDs"
}

###

### Test 11: Test basic dice rolling
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/game/dice/roll
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "notation": "1d20+5"
}

###

### Test 12: Test dice rolling with character context
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/game/dice/roll-with-character
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "notation": "1d20",
  "character_id": "{{characterId}}",
  "skill": "perception"
}

###

### Test 13: Get character details (verify character exists)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/game/character/{{characterId}}
Accept: application/json

###

### Test 14: Get campaign details (verify campaign exists)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/game/campaign/{{campaignId}}
Accept: application/json

###

### Test 15: Test image generation (may fail due to Azure config)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/game/generate-image
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "image_type": "scene_illustration",
  "details": {
    "location": "tavern",
    "mood": "welcoming",
    "time": "evening"
  }
}

###

### Test 16: Test battle map generation (may fail due to Azure config)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/game/battle-map
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "environment": {
    "location": "dungeon room",
    "terrain": "stone",
    "size": "medium"
  }
}

###

### Test 17: Test AI assistance endpoint
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/game/campaign/ai-assist
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "text": "The heroes enter a dark cave",
  "context_type": "description",
  "campaign_tone": "adventurous"
}

###

### Test 18: Test empty message validation
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/game/input
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "",
  "character_id": "{{characterId}}",
  "campaign_id": "{{campaignId}}"
}

###
